Pre-Game Insights: The Los Angeles Dodgers enter the series with a three-game lead over the San Diego Padres in the National League West.
The Colorado Rockies are mathematically eliminated from postseason contention but aim to play spoiler for the Dodgers.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Rockies have won six of their last ten games, showing improved performance.The series is crucial for the Dodgers as they seek to secure their eleventh division title in twelve seasons.
Others: Pitching matchups include Walker Buehler, Yoshinobu Yamamoto, and others on the Dodgers' side.The Rockies' Kris Bryant is out for the season due to a back injury.
